" Find parts of a word like re or retu or return:
/\<re\%[turn]\>
" In code:
if wrd == "re" || wrd == "ret" || wrd == "retu" || wrd == "retur"                                
  "do something
endif
" is now more cleanly represented as:
if match(wrd, "\\<re\\%[tur]\\>") > -1
  "do something
endif

